00:26:37.990 --> 00:26:41.460
But as Martin Luther King said in
1968 at Grosse Pointe High School,

00:26:41.460 --> 00:26:44.350
"You know, these are two
Americas living side by side."

00:26:44.350 --> 00:26:46.370
And we wanted to be very,
very honest about that --

00:26:46.370 --> 00:26:50.660
and so for Jason to write out of
his cultural experience and for me

00:26:50.660 --> 00:26:53.490
to write out of mine and to
speak very openly and honestly

00:26:53.490 --> 00:26:56.080
about white privilege and
-- as I mentioned earlier --

00:26:56.080 --> 00:27:00.150
the harm that it causes
many folks in our country.

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:02.830
So we wanted to do it
together because it felt

00:27:02.830 --> 00:27:06.510
like it was right way to do that.

00:27:06.510 --> 00:27:12.580
And we had so much trust built
between us that when it came

00:27:12.580 --> 00:27:18.310
to the writing process we just
let each other do what we did.

00:27:18.310 --> 00:27:21.570
And we wrote the book side by side,
checking in with each other --

00:27:21.570 --> 00:27:26.840
like we would if we were
walking through DC and, you know,

00:27:26.840 --> 00:27:29.960
going into a bank and having
two different experiences.

00:27:29.960 --> 00:27:33.270
Or if we are walking in Boston
and going into a restaurant

00:27:33.270 --> 00:27:35.310
and literally, side by side,

00:27:35.310 --> 00:27:37.180
still having two very
different experiences

00:27:37.180 --> 00:27:41.710
because of the inherent
racism in our country.

00:27:41.710 --> 00:27:44.170
So we had to just tackle
that together,

00:27:44.170 --> 00:27:45.650
and it was the best way to do it.

00:27:45.650 --> 00:27:48.720
And by the way, I'll forever,
forever, forever be grateful

00:27:48.720 --> 00:27:50.910
that I got to work on
a project like that

00:27:50.910 --> 00:27:54.200
with such an unbelievably
amazing human being.

00:27:54.200 --> 00:28:00.630
So thank you for giving
me the chance to say that.

00:28:00.630 --> 00:28:01.930
Hi.

00:28:01.930 --> 00:28:03.830
&gt;&gt; Is there going to
