00:29:02.820 --> 00:29:05.710 position:56%
So I - I'll take this last question.

00:29:05.710 --> 00:29:07.010
&gt;&gt; All right.

00:29:07.010 --> 00:29:12.250
So your book "The Gospel of Winter"
was about a young boy dealing

00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:13.970
with the crisis in
the Catholic Church.

00:29:13.970 --> 00:29:15.270
&gt;&gt; Brendan Kiely: Yeah.

00:29:15.270 --> 00:29:16.570
&gt;&gt; And so I was wondering,
from your own background

00:29:16.570 --> 00:29:20.070
and your own growing
up, how did that writing

00:29:20.070 --> 00:29:24.330
and that final book
work with your family,

00:29:24.330 --> 00:29:26.120
with your own personal connections?

00:29:26.120 --> 00:29:28.960
You know, how did that
work in that dynamic?

00:29:28.960 --> 00:29:30.820
&gt;&gt; Brendan Kiely: I deeply,
deeply appreciate that you bring

00:29:30.820 --> 00:29:32.120
up "The Gospel of Winter."

00:29:32.120 --> 00:29:33.420
Thank you so much.

00:29:33.420 --> 00:29:37.170
It is a very important book in
my relationship with my family --

00:29:37.170 --> 00:29:38.600
which I'll answer very quickly.

00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:41.090
But I will say this: Whether
it's "The Gospel of Winter"

00:29:41.090 --> 00:29:43.810
or "All American Boys" or
"The Last True Love Story,"

00:29:43.810 --> 00:29:45.860
I think the fundamentals
that are key

00:29:45.860 --> 00:29:47.730 position:56%
to me whenever I approach a book is,

00:29:47.730 --> 00:29:51.490
how do I help portray
the act of listening?

00:29:51.490 --> 00:29:57.560
How do I portray this
discussion about love?

00:29:57.560 --> 00:30:00.920
And those are those two - those
are the two things that are key,

00:30:00.920 --> 00:30:04.820
I think, to the third pillar --
which is, how do we get a person

00:30:04.820 --> 00:30:08.040
to stand up when things are
going wrong in society, right?

00:30:08.040 --> 00:30:11.120
I want to help people, and
young people in particular,

00:30:11.120 --> 00:30:13.570
feel like they have a roadmap
to learn how to listen,

00:30:13.570 --> 00:30:15.320
to get to the road to empathy,

00:30:15.320 --> 00:30:18.560
and that they know what
love is in its many forms.

00:30:18.560 --> 00:30:21.430
And then they can stand up
and do something about it.

00:30:21.430 --> 00:30:23.520
And so for me, writing
"The Gospel of Winter" --

00:30:23.520 --> 00:30:27.400 position:56%
which is a story about a 16-year-old
boy who is trying to decide whether

00:30:27.400 --> 00:30:31.470
or not he will let the world know
he has been abused by his priest --

00:30:31.470 --> 00:30:34.610
was a very powerful experience
for me to write about,

00:30:34.610 --> 00:30:37.080
coming from an Irish
Catholic background in Boston,

00:30:37.080 --> 00:30:40.960 position:56%
going to Catholic school my whole
life, having a huge Catholic family.

00:30:40.960 --> 00:30:48.100
And I was extremely nervous when
in - when writing the story.

00:30:48.100 --> 00:30:51.740
In - as I tried my best, though,

00:30:51.740 --> 00:30:54.130
it's not a book about
blaming people.

00:30:54.130 --> 00:30:57.780
And I don't think any of my
books are about blaming people,

00:30:57.780 --> 00:31:01.930
but instead helping us think
about being honest and letting

00:31:01.930 --> 00:31:05.870
that become a part
of our road to love.

00:31:05.870 --> 00:31:10.610 position:56%
I will end with this, because the
person that made me the most nervous

00:31:10.610 --> 00:31:13.050
to read the book was my
grandmother, who is the matriarch

00:31:13.050 --> 00:31:16.070
of the family -- also the
woman who I was with in Ireland

00:31:16.070 --> 00:31:20.550
when I was touring Ireland,
you know, with my grandfather,

00:31:20.550 --> 00:31:24.580
and to whom this book is
dedicated along with my wife.

00:31:24.580 --> 00:31:28.500
Because she said to me, when
she read the book, "Brendan,

00:31:28.500 --> 00:31:31.530
your book 'The Gospel
of Winter' reminds me

00:31:31.530 --> 00:31:35.290
of Solomon asking God
for a listening heart."

00:31:35.290 --> 00:31:38.150
And for me, I still have
goose bumps just repeating

00:31:38.150 --> 00:31:41.070
that because that's
my goal, you know --

00:31:41.070 --> 00:31:44.030
to help us think about how
to have a listening heart.

00:31:44.030 --> 00:31:46.480
And that's my goal in all my books.

00:31:46.480 --> 00:31:48.970
So I appreciate that.

00:31:48.970 --> 00:31:51.510
Thank you Grandma [laughs].

